  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Meyer's NT Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 17:8-9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἐτάραξαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] This was alarm at revolutionary outrage and Roman vengeance. Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 2:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λαβόντες τὸ ἱκανόν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 15:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὸ ἱκανὸν ποιεῖν τινι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is to satisfy one, so that he can demand nothing more. Therefore: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "after they had received satisfaction",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", so that for the present they might desist from further claims against the persons of the accused, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "satisdatione accepta",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Comp. Grotius. But whether this satisfaction took place by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "furnishing sureties",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " or by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "lodging a deposit of money",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", remains undecided; certainly its object was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a guarantee that no attempt against the Roman majesty should prevail or should occur",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This is evident from the relation in which ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λαβόντες τὸ ἱκανόν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " necessarily stands with the point of complaint (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 17:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and with the disquietude (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐτάραξαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") excited thereby. Therefore the opinions are to be rejected, that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λαβ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἱκ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". refers to security that Paul and Silas would appear in case of need before the court (Grotius, Raphel), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "or",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that they would be no longer sheltered (Michaelis, Heinrichs, comp. Ewald), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "or",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that they should immediately depart (Heumann, Kuinoel). Moreover, it is erroneous, with Luther and Camerarius, to suppose that by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὸ ἱκανόν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is meant a satisfactory ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "vindication",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Luke would certainly have brought out this more definitely; and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λαβόντες",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " denotes an actual ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "receipt",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the satisfaction (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὸ ἱκανόν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), as the context suggests nothing else.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Observe, too, how here (it is otherwise in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 16:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") the politarchs did not prosecute the matter further, but cut it short with the furnished guarantee, which was at least politically the most prudent course.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
